definition.value: A monounsaturated fatty aldehyde that is hex-2-enal substituted by an ethyl group at position 2.
A p-menthadiene with double bonds at positions 2 and 4(8).
A methyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of cyclohexanecarboxylic acid with methanol.
The organic bromide salt of a 5alpha androstane compound having 3alpha-hydroxy-, 17beta-acetoxy-, 2beta-morpholino- and 16beta-N-allyllyrrolidinium substituents.
An alkene that is heptane which carries a methylidene group at position 3.
A 3-octene in which the double bond adopts a cis-configuration.
A 3-octene in which the double bond adopts a trans-configuration.

A butenolide that is furan-2(5H)-one substituted by a phenyl group at position 3 and by a p-(methylsulfonyl)phenyl group at position 4. A selective cyclooxygenase 2 inhibitor, it was used from 1999 to 2004 for the treatment of ostoarthritis, but was withdrawn following concerns about an associated increased risk of heart attack and stroke.
